 Understand What the Script Will Do
Before you write a single line, here's the plain-English logic of log_concept.py:

Ask the user: "What concept did you study?" → store it as a string
Ask the user: "Rate your confidence from 1 to 5" → store it as a number
Create a dictionary (like a small record) with: concept name, confidence score, and today's date
Open the concepts.json file (or create it if it doesn't exist)
Load any existing records from it
Add the new record to the list
Save everything back to the file
Print a confirmation message

This is just Python basics — input(), dictionaries, lists, and file handling. Nothing beyond what you already know, except possibly file handling, which I'll explain as we go.